    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa6c5d1e_7597e35e",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 177,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T21:48:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Rationale: this is named for consistency with Array.prototype.map()[1].\n\nA typical use case for this method is as a replacement for the following pattern when using raw DOM nodes:\n\n  const innertTexts \u003d element.querySelectorAll(\u0027p\u0027).map((p) \u003d\u003e p.innerText);\n\nWith a PageObjectElement, this would be written as:\n\n  const innerTexts \u003d await poe.$map(\u0027p\u0027, (p) \u003d\u003e p.innerText);",
      "parentUuid": "dcc7dde7_2e972304",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 177,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 177,
        "endChar": 12
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d66b5630_ba93471f",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 183,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T17:48:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This appears to the be same as $map/applyFnToSelectorAll except with no return value. Do we need both?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 183,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 183,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fa578db8_2c321930",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 183,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T21:48:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The difference is semantic. If client code uses $map instead of $each, the reader will assume that the code cares about the return value, which might not be true.\n\nThis is analogous to Array.prototype.map()[1] vs. Array.prototype.forEach()[2].\n\n[1] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/map\n[2] https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Array/forEach",
      "parentUuid": "d66b5630_ba93471f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 183,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 183,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e119fb16_1cec632c",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 191,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T17:48:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Either $$find to be consistent with other APIs (in that this only returns one element) or be more verbose findDescendantWithSelector or slightly more verbose findDescendant",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 191,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 191,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "924e7221b337648179b21b7f2e4b6e1dc350bba3",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a5d29d40_fa77c9e2",
        "filename": "infra-sk/modules/page_object/page_object_element.ts",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 191,
      "author": {
        "id": 10009
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-06T21:48:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The reason this is named $$find and not $find is that it\u0027s a replacement for the following pattern when using raw DOM nodes, which is used when a query selector does not suffice:\n\n  // Using the native API.\n  const p \u003d element.querySelectorAll(\u0027p\u0027).find((p) \u003d\u003e p.innerText.startsWith(\u0027Hello\u0027));\n\n  // Or equivalently, using common-sk.\n  const p \u003d $(\u0027p\u0027).find((p) \u003d\u003e p.innerText.startsWith(\u0027Hello\u0027));\n\nSince the pattern uses $/querySelectorAll and Array.prototype.find, it makes sense to me to name this $find.\n\nNaming this method $$find would feel a bit weird to me given the underlying querySelectorAll call (as opposed to querySelector).\n\nLet me know if you still disagree and I\u0027ll be happy to rename it as you suggested.",
      "parentUuid": "e119fb16_1cec632c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 191,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 191,
        "endChar": 13
      },
